frica east to southern Australia. First recorded in South Africa in Durban between the late 1960s and early 1970s, possibly having spread from Zanzibar. Established in Cape Town in the early 1990s, perhaps from ship-assisted birds from Durban; founder population was fewer than 20 birds. Still confined to these two centres and Richards Bay. Impacts: Preys on eggs and nestlings of native birds, also eats small native animals. Mobs humans and pets. Potential air-strike hazard at Cape Town international Airport due to a nearby roost, which has now been removed. Occasionally destroys vegetable gardens in informal settlements. Vector for pathogens that cause cholera, typhoid, dysentery and salmonella poisoning','Towns and cities.','alien','2018-01-05 08:17:58','anim17.jpg:','1','','2017-12-10 14:38:18',NULL,NULL,NULL),(135,23,'','','Mammalia','','Lagomorpha','','Leporidae','','Oryctolagus','','cuniculus','','European rabbit','','','',NULL,'','','2017-12-10 12:44:19','anim7.jpg:','5',NULL,'2017-12-10 12:44:19',NULL,NULL,NULL),(136,49,'','','Aves','','','','','','Threskiornis','','aethiopicus','','Sacred Ibis','','','','','','','2018-01-05 10:25:38','anim34.png:','5','','2017-12-16 20:10:29',NULL,NULL,NULL),(137,49,'','','Aves','','','','','','Threskiornis','','aethiopicus','','Sacred Ibis','','','','','','','2018-01-06 14:39:04','anim48.jpg:anim34.png:','5','','2018-01-05 10:25:38',NULL,NULL,NULL),(138,58,'','','Insecta','','Thysanura','','Lepismatidae','','Ctenolepisma','','longicaudata','','Grey silverfish (Eng), Grys visit (Afr)','','','',NULL,'','','2018-01-05 09:15:14','anim45.jpg:','1',NULL,'2018-01-05 09:15:14',NULL,NULL,NULL),(139,36,'','','Aves','','Passeriformes','','Passeridae','','Passer','','domesticus','','House sparrow','','','','','','','2017-12-10 14:48:56','anim21.jpg:anim20.jpg:','1','','2017-12-10 13:40:34',NULL,NULL,NULL),(140,36,'','','Aves','','Passeriformes','','Passeridae','','Passer','','domesticus','','House sparrow','','','','','','','2018-01-08